 retrieveRuntimeField functionalities. I wonder if there are any issues with Java fields or whether the Scala compiler might optimize calls unexpectedly. It seems that using JsonCodecMaker may also have limitations regarding local dependencies.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing support class packaging**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering that the needed package of support classes might be located in test packages, and user-code-filtering could be excluding everything else. It seems like dynamic access to support may not be tracked unless it involves library calls. For native images, I wonder if generated codecs reference MacroRuntimeNames, but it looks like the macro evaluates field names to constants instead. \\\\n\\\\nSo, perhaps the macroSupport runtime isn’t really necessary. I note potential issues with sourceSets and the order of test dependencies in build.gradle. Regarding test classes, I think using underscores might be a good idea, and I'll summarize everything concisely without running tests as instructed.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_ZUyhFJxbSwHIYzqovHHqyOlW|fc_05db16ac799a99ce0169f881b00dc4819c8add1fb2316144be\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/src/test/scala/com_github_plokhotnyuk_jsoniter_scala/jsoniter_scala_macros_3/CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeTest.scala\", \"limit\": 220}}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_hliiz1ryLLA6QB3JCKwpaxlu|fc_05db16ac799a99ce0169f881b00ddc819c89bdc7664dcd36de\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/build.gradle\", \"limit\": 120}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 777, \"output\": 1084, \"cacheRead\": 38912, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 40773, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\