 property might not include the actual jars unless it's explicitly configured. It seems like the runtime compiler isn't supported in native environments. However, in the JVM, the java.class.path does include the test runtime. I might need to include the destination output temp as well. Dotty may require an output directory, and I’m also wondering if Main.process could write the .class files without the need to load them.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating potential issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm recognizing a potential issue with the native image in `dotty.tools.dotc.Main.process`, as it requires a lot of resources. I wonder if we might need to catch an Exception rather than Throwable, as catching Error seems necessary here. Tests could fail under native if an Exception is thrown, highlighting the dynamic nature of runtime compilers that may produce an UnsupportedFeatureError. I realize that using `$` in file or class names might cause problems, so I think we should keep a one-to-one structure in dedicated files and ensure to import NativeImageSupport.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_gaZ4EBY0Dth89HThDFdcgVXe|fc_05db16ac799a99ce0169f882653a78819c8b36b2b79834f485\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"NativeImageSupport\\\" tests/src -g '*.scala' -g '*.java' | head -50\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1159, \"output\": 977, \"cacheRead\": 36352, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 38488, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777893971767, \"responseId\": \"resp_05db16ac799a99ce0169f882545494819c813cd6b2b5d730e6\"}}\n2864:  tests/src/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/1.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_wildfly_openssl/wildfly_openssl_java/SSLTest.java:                if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n2866