e, \"timestamp\": 1777894264871}]}\n4386:[thinking] **Explaining code errors**\n4388:[thinking] I need to be concise while explaining the root cause of the issue. The problem arises because the Scala anonymous partial function is applying an erased object, and the library's compile-time evaluation reflection expects an apply(String) method, which leads to errors. To resolve this, we changed the support mappers to a Java class that properly implements apply(String) and isDefinedAt(String). I should also mention that there's no runtime involved in this resolution.\n4395:[assistant] - The Scala anonymous `PartialFunction` instances compiled to `apply(Object)`, but `CompileTimeEval$QuoteScope` reflects with the runtime argument type and looks for `apply(String)`.\n4404:[assistant] - Improved the compiler assertion message to print actual compiler errors:\n4410:[assistant] - `tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/src/test/scala/.../CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeTest.scala`\n4414:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Explaining code errors**\\n\\nI need to be concise while explaining the root cause of the issue. The problem arises because the Scala anonymous partial function is applying an erased object, and the library's compile-time evaluation reflection expects an apply(String) method, which leads to errors. To resolve this, we changed the support mappers to a Java class that properly implements apply(String) and isDefinedAt(String). I should also mention that there's no runtime involved in this resolution.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_05db16ac799a99ce0169f8837a7794819c8e941d0d5bdcba39\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-IN9A-GMIwkw0oxQXeD4DAS3fYTRRkfSVuUhDhJ5K1tOVaPBNLtKbRNsFxNgoX7FB9z4c5VjVI5f3I6cUC9Y6UuVnQqWwJagVVSeA6V6_8BK4VDbZO6ZMUJwZr0trqdfdjZOq7igPpeCl_aTl4Arur1dRPvVYzrcdxSij